'''Fr. Anthony Joseph Crean''' (13 June 1911 – 21 March 1975) was an English [[Roman Catholic]] [[priest]] who was [[murder]]ed by [[serial killer]] [[Patrick Mackay]].<ref>[http://www.crimeandinvestigation.co.uk/crime-files/patrick-mackay/crimes ''Crime Files:'' Patrick Mackay]; Crime and Investigation</ref>
Crean was born in [[Brentford]], [[Middlesex]], England. Fr. Crean had served the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gibraltar|Gibraltar Diocese]], and was in semi-retirement he was acting as [[chaplain]] in [[Shorne]], [[Kent]], at the time of his murder.<ref>[http://www.stjohnsgravesend.org.uk/history/ History] St. John's Church, Gravesend</ref> On 22 March 1975, Mackay murdered Creane with an axe in the small Shorne cottage he lived in.<ref>[http://www.sonsofdivineprovidence.org/SDPHistory/shorne.htm Shorne] Sons of Divine Providence</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Odell|first1=Robin|last2=Gregg|first2=Wilfred|title=Murderers' Row: An International Murderers' Who's Who|date=2011|publisher=The History Press|isbn=9780752471280|page=267|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hqkTDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT267|accessdate=6 June 2017|language=en}}</ref>
